    "Upon examining the distribution of incorrect answers, they The accessibility of ChatGPT in the pharmacological test set based on Levenshtein similarity consistency tests; d: The accessibility of ChatGPT in the pharmacological test set based on entity similarity consistency testswere found to be scattered.",
    "It is speculated that the reason for these incorrect answers may be associated with the frequency of drug molecular formulas in the training tasks of GPT-3.5 rather than the difficulty level of the queries (Table 2, Fig.",
